    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const articles = $input.all().map(item => item.json);\n\nconst grouped = articles.map((a, i) =>\n`${i + 1}. ${a.title} - ${a.url} (${a.source})`\n).join('\\n');\n\nconst prompt = `\nYou are a senior frontend editor writing a high-quality weekly newsletter.\n\nUsing the articles below:\n\n${grouped}\n\nWrite a concise, insight-driven newsletter.\n\nSTRICT RULES:\n\n- Generate ONLY inner content blocks.\n- Do NOT include <html>, <body>, or outer wrapper tables.\n- Use clean semantic HTML only.\n- Return ONLY valid HTML.\n\nUse this exact structure:\n\n<h1>Frontend Weekly</h1>\n\n<h2>Performance & Tooling</h2>\n<p>...</p>\n<a href=\"URL\">Read Full Breakdown</a>\n\n<h2>AI & Developer Experience</h2>\n<p>...</p>\n<a href=\"URL\">Read Full Breakdown</a>\n\n<h2>Architecture & Patterns</h2>\n<p>...</p>\n<a href=\"URL\">Read Full Breakdown</a>\n\n<h2>Recommended Reads</h2>\n<p>Short curated list with anchor links</p>\n\nAdditional rules:\n- Professional tone for senior frontend engineers\n- Avoid fluff\n- Avoid generic greetings\n- 350–450 words\n- End with a short CTA paragraph linking to https://elegantfrontend.training\n\nReturn ONLY valid HTML.\n`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { prompt } }];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [208, 128],
      "id": "3c2c245b-ab3b-45fe-a976-ad1b71de3b19",
      "name": "Code in JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://host.docker.internal:11434/api/generate",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"llama3.2:3b\",\n  \"prompt\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.prompt) }},\n  \"stream\": false\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
